---
import {
	Container,
	FeatureCard,
	TextCardSection,
	StickyTextImageSection,
} from '@components/odyssey-theme';
import Layout from '../layouts/Page.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/sections/heros/HeroSection.astro';
import GetStartedSection from '../components/sections/GetStartedSection.astro';

const seo = {
	title: 'Locations | Experience Africa Safaris',
	description:
 		'Explore parks, lodges and reserves across Southern Africa — Kruger, Okavango, Namibia, Zimbabwe. Learn about our operating locations, accommodations and travel tips.',
};
---

<Layout {seo}>
	<HeroSection>
		<div slot="text-container">
			<h1>Explore game parks by locations</h1>
			<p>
				Learn about our operating locations and read our reviews of parks,
				lodges and reserves.
			</p>
		</div>
		<picture slot="image-container">
			<img
				src="/assets/images_converted/Nxai pan-51.webp"
				alt="Curteis Roberts"
				id="home-hero-image"
			/>
		</picture>
	</HeroSection>
	<Container>
		<section class="feature-card__section">
			<div class="feature-card__grid">
				<FeatureCard
					href="#south-africa"
					title="South Africa"
					imgSrc="assets/images/home/screenshots/Kruger-35-of-38"
				/>
				<FeatureCard
					href="#Botswana"
					title="Botswana"
					imgSrc="/assets/images/home/screenshots/Kgalagadi-Nossob"
				/>
				<FeatureCard
					href="#Zambia"
					title="Zambia"
					imgSrc="/assets/images/home/screenshots/Animals-11-of-35"
				/>
				<FeatureCard
					href="#Zimbabwe"
					title="Zimbabwe"
					imgSrc="/assets/images/home/screenshots/Kruger-20-of-47"
				/>
				<FeatureCard
					href="#Namibia"
					title="Namibia"
					imgSrc="/assets/images/home/screenshots/BirdDance"
				/>
			</div>
		</section>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<TextCardSection>
			<h2 id="south-africa">South Africa</h2>
			<strong>Parks, Game Reserves and Others</strong>
		</TextCardSection>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<StickyTextImageSection>
			<div slot="text-container">
				<h3>Kgalagadi Transfrontier Parka</h3>
				<p>
					This vast red-sand wilderness, shared with Botswana, offers excellent
					predator sightings, especially of black-maned lions. It's a true
					escape into a stark and beautiful desert landscape, perfect for
					photographers seeking unique shots. The sparse vegetation makes
					wildlife spotting easier than in denser bush. The best time to visit
					is during the cooler, dry months from May to September, when animals
					are more active.
				</p>
				<h3>Kruger National Park</h3>
				<p>
					One of Africa's most famous and accessible safari destinations,
					offering a classic Big Five experience. The park has a wide variety of
					habitats and an extensive road network, allowing for both self-drive
					and guided tours. Its diverse wildlife and stunning landscapes make it
					a premier safari location. The dry season, from May to October, is
					optimal for game viewing as vegetation thins out and animals gather at
					water sources.
				</p>
			</div>
			<picture slot="image-container">
				<img
					src="/assets/images_converted/Moditlo (23 of 24).webp"
					alt="Lion in the Kruger"
					loading="lazy"
				/>
			</picture>
		</StickyTextImageSection>
		<StickyTextImageSection reversed={true}>
			<div slot="text-container">
				<h3>Mountain Zebra National Park</h3>
				<p>
					A conservation success story focused on protecting the endangered Cape
					mountain zebra. This peaceful park in the Eastern Cape's Cradock
					region offers beautiful mountain scenery, diverse wildlife including
					cheetah and caracal, and a chance to experience a different side of
					South African wilderness. This park can be visited year-round, but the
					spring and autumn months offer particularly pleasant weather.
				</p>
				<h3>Cape Point</h3>
				<p>
					Located at the tip of the Cape Peninsula, this is a spectacular nature
					reserve with dramatic cliffs, beautiful fynbos, and breathtaking views
					where the Atlantic and Indian Oceans meet. While not a traditional
					safari destination, it offers great birdwatching and is home to
					baboons, ostriches, and unique flora. It's best to visit from
					September to March, during the spring and summer, when the weather is
					warm and wildflowers are in bloom.
				</p>
			</div>
			<picture slot="image-container">
				<img
					src="/assets/images_converted/Zebra-1.webp"
					alt="Lion in the Kruger"
					loading="lazy"
				/>
			</picture>
		</StickyTextImageSection>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<TextCardSection>
			<h2 id="Botswana">Botswana</h2>
			<strong>Parks, Game Reserves and Others</strong>
		</TextCardSection>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<StickyTextImageSection>
			<div slot="text-container">
				<h3>Moremi Game Reserve</h3>
				<p>
					The Moremi Game Reserve is a highlight of the Okavango Delta. Known
					for its lush landscapes that include lagoons, forests, and
					floodplains, the reserve supports a wide and diverse range of
					wildlife. As a key part of the Okavango Delta, it offers an
					exceptional safari experience. The dry season from June to October is
					ideal, as wildlife congregates at permanent water sources.
				</p>
				<h3>Khwai Community Concession</h3>
				<p>
					The Khwai Community Concession is renowned for its exceptional
					wildlife sightings, particularly around the Khwai River. This area is
					a prime example of a successful community-run tourism initiative,
					offering a great and authentic safari experience that directly
					benefits local people and conservation efforts. Wildlife viewing is
					excellent during the dry season, from May to October, when animals are
					concentrated near the river.
				</p>
				<h3>Savuti (Chobe National Park)</h3>
				<p>
					Savuti, a famous area within Chobe National Park, is a thrilling
					destination for observing predator action. The region is particularly
					famous for its elephants, which are often seen congregating around the
					Savuti Channel. It's a rugged and exciting part of Botswana's northern
					safari circuit. The best time to witness the high concentration of
					elephants is during the dry season, from May to November.
				</p>
				<h3>Makgadikgadi Salt Pans</h3>
				<p>
					The Makgadikgadi Salt Pans are a vast and surreal landscape,
					representing one of the largest salt pan systems in the world. The
					area is incredibly stark and can feel very lonely, creating a unique
					atmosphere of immense emptiness that is both haunting and beautiful.
					The dry season (April to October) is the best time to visit for a true
					sense of the desolate vastness and to see the famous meerkats.
				</p>
			</div>
			<picture slot="image-container">
				<img
					src="/assets/images_converted/Portal Eyes.webp"
					alt="Lion in the Kruger"
					loading="lazy"
				/>
			</picture>
		</StickyTextImageSection>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<StickyTextImageSection reversed={true}>
			<div slot="text-container">
				<h3>Kubu Island</h3>
				<p>
					Kubu Island is a granite outcrop in the middle of the Sua Pan. It is
					home to a collection of magnificent baobab trees that stand on the
					edge of the vast salt pan. This remote site is considered ancient and
					has a spiritual significance to the local communities. The dry season
					from April to October is the most accessible time to visit, as the pan
					is dry and can be driven on.
				</p>
				<h3>Meerkat Colony</h3>
				<p>
					A visit to a Meerkat Colony in Botswana offers an unforgettable
					experience with these small mammals. The meerkats are often habituated
					to human presence, allowing visitors to get up close and personal with
					the curious and adorable creatures as they go about their daily lives.
					Meerkats are visible year-round, but the cooler months from May to
					September are more comfortable for observing them.
				</p>
				<h3>Chobe National Park</h3>
				<p>
					Chobe National Park is celebrated for having the world's highest
					concentration of elephants. Visitors can witness massive large
					elephant herds along the Chobe River, which forms the park's northern
					boundary. This rich and productive ecosystem is teeming with a variety
					of wildlife. The dry season (May to October) is prime time for seeing
					large elephant herds along the river.
				</p>
				<h3>Mashatu Game Reserve</h3>
				<p>
					Mashatu Game Reserve is a privately owned reserve often called the
					"Land of Giants" due to its impressive populations of elephants,
					baobab trees, and large predators. This private reserve offers a great
					and exclusive safari experience, focusing on high-quality sightings
					and a more intimate bush experience. The dry winter months, from June
					to October, offer the best game viewing opportunities.
				</p>
			</div>
			<picture slot="image-container">
				<img
					src="/assets/images_converted/Kruger (1 of 47).webp"
					alt="Lion in the Kruger"
					loading="lazy"
				/>
			</picture>
		</StickyTextImageSection>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<TextCardSection>
			<h2 id="Zambia">Zambia</h2>
			<strong>Parks, Game Reserves and Others</strong>
		</TextCardSection>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<StickyTextImageSection>
			<div slot="text-container">
				<h3>South Luangwa National Park</h3>
				<p>
					Known for walking safaris and leopards, it is considered one of the
					greatest wildlife sanctuaries in the world, with a high density of
					game and professional guides. The Luangwa River is the lifeblood of
					the park, attracting a diverse range of animals. The best time for
					walking safaris and game viewing is the dry season, from April to
					October.
				</p>
				<h3>Liuwa Plains National Park</h3>
				<p>
					Home to Africa's second-largest wildebeest migration. This vast,
					remote grassland is a truly wild and exclusive destination. It's also
					famous for its large hyena clans and abundant birdlife, offering a
					safari experience far from the crowds. The wildebeest migration peaks
					in the rainy season, from November to April, while the drier months
					are better for general game viewing.
				</p>
				<h3>Lower Zambezi National Park</h3>
				<p>
					Spectacular for river safaris and canoeing. Situated opposite Mana
					Pools, it offers incredible views of the Zambezi River and the
					escarpment. The park is renowned for its large herds of elephants,
					hippos, and buffalo, making it a diverse wildlife haven. The dry
					season, from June to October, is the best time for game viewing as
					animals gather at the river.
				</p>
			</div>
			<picture slot="image-container">
				<img
					src="/assets/images_converted/Giraffe Sun (30 of 32).webp"
					alt="Lion in the Kruger"
					loading="lazy"
				/>
			</picture>
		</StickyTextImageSection>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<TextCardSection>
			<h2 id="Zimbabwe">Zimbabwe</h2>
			<strong>Parks, Game Reserves and Others</strong>
		</TextCardSection>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<StickyTextImageSection reversed={true}>
			<div slot="text-container">
				<h3>Mana Pools National Park</h3>
				<p>
					Famous for walking and canoeing safaris. The park's floodplain,
					bordered by the Zambezi River, provides stunning scenery and
					incredible opportunities to get up close to elephants and other
					wildlife on foot. It’s an authentic and highly sought-after wilderness
					experience. The dry season, from May to October, is the most popular
					time to visit due to excellent game viewing opportunities.
				</p>
				<h3>Gonarezhou National Park</h3>
				<p>
					A rugged and beautiful park in the southeast, part of the Great
					Limpopo Transfrontier Park. Known for its massive baobab trees and the
					Chilojo Cliffs, it offers a true wilderness experience. The park is a
					haven for elephants and other large mammals, with fewer tourists. The
					dry season, from June to October, is best for both wildlife viewing
					and accessibility.
				</p>
				<h3>Hwange National Park</h3>
				<p>
					Zimbabwe's largest and most famous park is a haven for its immense
					elephant population. The park's diverse landscapes, from desert sands
					to grasslands, support a wide array of wildlife, including the Big
					Five and endangered wild dogs. It's a classic safari destination,
					renowned for its pumped waterholes that become bustling wildlife hubs
					in the dry season. The best time to visit is during the dry season,
					from July to October, for exceptional game viewing as animals
					congregate at waterholes.
				</p>
			</div>
			<picture slot="image-container">
				<img
					src="/assets/images_converted/A7III Etosh All-46.webp"
					alt="Lion in the Kruger"
					loading="lazy"
				/>
			</picture>
		</StickyTextImageSection>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<TextCardSection>
			<h2 id="Namibia">Namibia</h2>
			<strong>Parks, Game Reserves and Others</strong>
		</TextCardSection>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<StickyTextImageSection>
			<div slot="text-container">
				<h3>Fish River Canyon</h3>
				<p>
					The Fish River Canyon is Africa's largest canyon. This dramatic
					geological feature is a deeply carved, winding gorge that showcases
					the immense power of natural erosion over millions of years. Its
					ancient and rugged landscape is a powerful reminder of Earth's long
					and complex history. The best time to visit is during the cooler
					winter months, from May to September, when temperatures are ideal for
					hiking.
				</p>
				<h3>Sossusvlei</h3>
				<p>
					Sossusvlei is a place of spectacular beauty, known for its unique and
					breathtaking landscapes. The area is famous for its towering red
					dunes, which are among the highest in the world. This iconic Namibian
					destination offers a stunning contrast of deep orange sand against a
					vast blue sky. The most popular time to visit is the dry season (May
					to October) when the weather is mild and skies are clear, perfect for
					photography.
				</p>
				<h3>Etosha National Park</h3>
				<p>
					Etosha National Park is an incredibly open and expansive park, perfect
					for viewing great wildlife. It is especially famous for its numerous
					waterholes where a wide variety of animals, including elephants,
					lions, and giraffes, gather. This park provides a classic safari
					experience with excellent opportunities for wildlife photography. The
					best time for game viewing is during the dry season from June to
					October, when animals are concentrated around waterholes.
				</p>
				<h3>Caprivi Strip (Bwabwata National Park)</h3>
				<p>
					The Caprivi Strip, now home to Bwabwata National Park, is a region
					defined by its abundant water sources, including the Okavango and
					Zambezi rivers. This creates a lush and green environment, a stark
					contrast to the rest of Namibia. It's a key area for diverse wildlife,
					including a significant elephant population. The dry season, from May
					to October, is ideal for game viewing, though the lush landscapes are
					beautiful year-round.
				</p>
			</div>
			<picture slot="image-container">
				<img
					src="/assets/images_converted/Kudu (1 of 1).webp"
					alt="Lion in the Kruger"
					loading="lazy"
				/>
			</picture>
		</StickyTextImageSection>
	</Container>
	<Container>
		<GetStartedSection></GetStartedSection>
	</Container>
</Layout>

<style>
	.feature-card__section {
		margin: var(--section-margin) auto;
	}
	.feature-card__grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: var(--theme-grid-gap);
	}
	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.feature-card__grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
